                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/15275.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Alger</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mazatlan</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 5, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge receipt on June 4
                    of American declaration on the Mexican situation. I at once sent copies to the
                    Military Commander and the civil authorities for their information.</p>
                <p>I understand that the Military Commander on reading the message remarked, “What a
                    witty man Mr. Wilson is.” This is the only comment that I have heard. * * *</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. E. Alger.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
